						<summary>

						<p>This mutilated and damaged inscription is dated <hi rend="bold">Chāḷukya-Vikrama year 42, Hēma[ḷaṁbi], Āshāḍha • • • • • Sunday, Saṅkramaṇa.</hi> In Hēmaḷaṁbi, the Karkaṭaka-saṅkramaṇa which occurred in the month of Āshāḍha, fell on Tuesday = A.D. 1117, June 26. For want of details the date is not verifiable. The inscription seems to register a gift of gold.</p>						

						</summary>
